<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/100: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hall</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-07T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 7,
                                        1921—2 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>34. Your 36, March 17, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Informally ask Foreign Minister why American passports seized by Greek
                            authorities have not been returned in accordance with promise mentioned
                            in your 274, December 23, and renew request for return. Telegraph
                            reply.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>